Answer: Step 1: Prepare the heteroaryl electrophile by N-Boc protection of 5-chloro-1H-pyrrolo[2,3-b]pyridine, then C3 borylation to 5-chloro-1-Boc-pyrrolo[2,3-b]pyridine-3-boronic acid pinacol ester; Suzuki couple this with 4-chloro-2-fluoro-5-bromopyrimidine to give 4-chloro-2-fluoro-5-(5-chloro-1-Boc-pyrrolo[2,3-b]pyridin-3-yl)pyrimidine | Step 2: In parallel, from enantiopure tert-butyl ((1R,2R)-2-(hydroxymethyl)cyclohexyl)carbamate, convert CH2OH to mesylate/tosylate, displace with NaN3 to tert-butyl ((1R,2R)-2-(azidomethyl)cyclohexyl)carbamate, then reduce the azide to tert-butyl ((1R,2R)-2-(aminomethyl)cyclohexyl)carbamate | Step 3: Couple tert-butyl ((1R,2R)-2-(aminomethyl)cyclohexyl)carbamate with 4-chloro-2-fluoro-5-(5-chloro-1-Boc-pyrrolo[2,3-b]pyridin-3-yl)pyrimidine under SNAr conditions (e.g., DIPEA, heat) to replace the 4-chloro group and form tert-butyl ((1R,2R)-2-((2-fluoro-5-(5-chloro-1-Boc-pyrrolo[2,3-b]pyridin-3-yl)pyrimidin-4-yl)amino)methyl)cyclohexyl)carbamate | Step 4: Global Boc deprotection with TFA or HCl/dioxane to unveil the cyclohexyl primary amine and azaindole NH, furnishing N[C@@H]1CCCC[C@H]1CNc1nc(-c2c[nH]c3ncc(Cl)cc23)ncc1F.

